!begin_node (!kw [html_nodesize])
!html_name cmd_html_nodesize

Set size of headings (HTML only).

!begin_xlist [(!TYPEPOSITION)]

!item [(!TYPEPOSITION)] (!COMMAND), (!PREAMBLE) & (!MAINPART)

!item [(!SYNTAX)] (!T)!/html_nodesize (!VALUE)(!t)

!item [(!DESCRIPTION)]
You can set the font size of the HTML headlines with this switch. By
default UDO will use  value of 1. That means, that UDO will output
(!code [<h1>...</h1>]) for chapters, (!code [<h2>...</h2>]) for sections
etc. The example shows how to tell UDO that it should output
(!code [<h2>...</h2>]) for chapters etc.

!item [(!EXAMPLE)]
(!T)!/html_nodesize 2(!t)

!item [(!EXISTSSINCE)] Release~5 Patchlevel~4

!item [(!SEEALSO)]
(!KW [node]), (!KW [subnode]), (!KW [subsubnode]), (!KW [subsubsubnode])

!end_xlist

!end_node
